From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Pavel Shirshov <pavel@7mind.io>
Date: Tue, 12 May 2026 14:15:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] [SYCL] Enable BF16 convert path on open-source DPC++

Upstream gates the bf16 case of `ggml_get_to_fp16_sycl` (and the
`ggml_get_to_fp16_nc_sycl` variant) behind:

    #if defined(__INTEL_LLVM_COMPILER)
        #if __has_include(<sycl/ext/oneapi/bfloat16.hpp>)
            ...

`__INTEL_LLVM_COMPILER` is only set by Intel's proprietary `icpx`/`dpcpp`
distribution. nixpkgs builds DPC++ from the open-source `intel/llvm`
upstream which exposes the same SYCL interface (including
`<sycl/ext/oneapi/bfloat16.hpp>` and `sycl::ext::oneapi::bfloat16`) but
identifies as plain Clang and does NOT define `__INTEL_LLVM_COMPILER`.

Effect: any model that mixes bf16 tensors with a quantized format (e.g.
gpt-oss:20b MXFP4 + bf16 norms / embeddings) aborts on first decode:

    ggml-sycl/convert.cpp:764: fatal error: unsupport data type=bf16

Reproduced on B70 with `ggml_backend_sched_graph_compute_async` →
`ggml_sycl_op_mul_mat_sycl` → fall-through to `GGML_ABORT`.

The `__has_include` check alone is sufficient — if the header is present
the bfloat16 type works (we already rely on `sycl::ext::oneapi::bfloat16`
in `set_rows.cpp` via the IMF-bypass postPatch, which compiles and runs
cleanly on B70 across granite / qwen / gemma).

This patch drops the proprietary-compiler gate and keeps the header
availability check.
---
 ggml/src/ggml-sycl/convert.cpp | 8 +++-----
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

--- a/ggml/src/ggml-sycl/convert.cpp
+++ b/ggml/src/ggml-sycl/convert.cpp
@@ -2,11 +2,9 @@
 #include "dequantize.hpp"
 #include "presets.hpp"
 
-#if defined(__INTEL_LLVM_COMPILER)
-    #if __has_include(<sycl/ext/oneapi/bfloat16.hpp>)
-        #include <sycl/ext/oneapi/bfloat16.hpp>
-        #define GGML_SYCL_HAS_BF16
-    #endif
+#if __has_include(<sycl/ext/oneapi/bfloat16.hpp>)
+    #include <sycl/ext/oneapi/bfloat16.hpp>
+    #define GGML_SYCL_HAS_BF16
 #endif
 
 template <int qk, int qr, dequantize_kernel_t dequantize_kernel, typename dst_t>
